t-max-width:48rem] mx-auto max-w-(--thread-content-max-width) flex-1 group/turn-messages focus-visible:outline-hidden relative flex w-full min-w-0 flex-col agent-turn"><div class="flex max-w-full flex-col gap-4 grow"><div data-message-author-role="assistant" data-message-id="36177636-b436-447a-9a11-77926f30e8f5" dir="auto" data-message-model-slug="gpt-5-3" class="min-h-8 text-message relative flex w-full flex-col items-end gap-2 text-start break-words whitespace-normal outline-none keyboard-focused:focus-ring [.text-message+&amp;]:mt-1"><div class="flex w-full flex-col gap-1 empty:hidden"><div class="markdown prose dark:prose-invert w-full wrap-break-word dark markdown-new-styling"><p data-start="0" data-end="269">Alright — calling it “exact clone” is where things get tricky.<br data-start="62" data-end="65">
You can absolutely build a <strong data-start="92" data-end="127">full-featured Dontpad-style app</strong>, but “exact” (same infra simplicity + real-time + scaling + zero-auth + persistence) requires a proper architecture, not just a small script.</p>
<p data-start="271" data-end="409">So I’ll give you a <strong data-start="290" data-end="316">production-level clone</strong> (real-time, multi-user, auto-save, shareable URLs) — this is very close to Dontpad behavior.</p>
<hr data-start="411" data-end="414">
<h1 data-section-id="ri4l6s" data-start="416" data-end="451">🚀 What you’ll build (Full Clone)</h1>
<ul data-start="452" data-end="638">
<li data-section-id="1qz3zrl" data-start="452" data-end="484">
<p data-start="454" data-end="484">Unique URL = unique document</p>
</li>
<li data-section-id="hl3r2d" data-start="485" data-end="534">
<p data-start="487" data-end="534">Real-time collaboration (instant typing sync)</p>
</li>
<li data-section-id="3d9r63" data-start="535" data-end="548">
<p data-start="537" data-end="548">Auto-save</p>
</li>
<li data-section-id="1bz55gq" data-start="549" data-end="590">
<p data-start="551" data-end="590">Multiple users editing simultaneously</p>
</li>
<li data-section-id="1p83uwn" data-start="591" data-end="623">
<p data-start="593" data-end="623">Persistent storage (MongoDB)</p>
</li>
<li data-section-id="1elik21" data-start="624" data-end="638">
<p data-start="626" data-end="638">Deployable</p>
</li>
</ul>
<hr data-start="640" data-end="643">
<h1 data-section-id="1y21n5p" data-start="645" data-end="660">🧱 Tech Stack</h1>
<ul data-start="661" data-end="776">
<li data-section-id="1ricu0m" data-start="661" data-end="705">
<p data-start="663" data-end="705">Backend: <strong data-start="672" data-end="705">Node.js + Express + Socket.IO</strong></p>
</li>
<li data-section-id="1nwrwb9" data-start="706" data-end="729">
<p data-start="708" data-end="729">Database: <strong data-start="718" data-end="729">MongoDB</strong></p>
</li>
<li data-section-id="de2r0n" data-start="730" data-end="776">
<p data-start="732" data-end="776">Frontend: <strong data-start="742" data-end="776">Vanilla JS (or React optional)</strong></p>
</li>
</ul>
